{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 10:37:06.477430", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission completed.\n\nSummary of what was submitted:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [ \"server_access_router\" ]\n- root_cause_name: [ \"ospf_area_misconfiguration\" ]\n\nNotes:\n- The diagnosis identified that the server_access_router is bridging the server-farm network (10.200.0.0/24) and advertising it into OSPF, making backend servers directly reachable from host subnets — a violation of the intended design that backends be accessible only via the load balancer.\n- The chosen root cause classification is \"ospf_area_misconfiguration\" to reflect that the OSPF advertisement of the server subnet is misaligned with the intended design/policy and is causing undesired reachability. If you prefer a more specific category (e.g., missing ACL or improper bridge configuration), let me know and I can resubmit with an alternate root cause label.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2117, "output_tokens": 188, "total_tokens": 2305, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
